		<title>12GROWTH IN HOME COMPUTING</title>
		<content> Early in 1985 a survey of 850 1st, 2nd
 and 3rd year pupils at Lasswade High  
 School Centre was done to find        
 information on{home microcomputer     
{ownership.}Of the 850 pupils 222 (26%)
 had a microcomputer in their home.    
 The rapid growth in computing as a    
 hobby is illustrated by the years in  
 which computers were bought and by    
 the percentage of the sample owning   
 computers in each year:               
                                       
{Year     No.        %                 
 1979       1      0.1                 
 1980       2      0.3                 
 1981       3      0.7                 
 1982      12      2.1                 
 1983      76     11.1                 
 1984     122     25.4                 
                                       
                                       
